main event: Observation of black smoke-like objects over International Airport in Washington, D.C. on December 12, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were observed on two consecutive evenings,The observer reported the objects as silent with bright white color,The objects moved rapidly and changed direction,One confirmed witness was involved in military and civilian investigations of UFOs,The sighting lasted for about 10-15 minutes before the objects disappeared rapidly.
witness description: A military trained individual with experience in classifying flying objects.
